<H1> <I>Sylloge Inscriptionum Graecarum:</I> 626</H1><BR>
<H2>A STATUE OF LYKORTAS AT EPIDAUROS</H2>
<I>Greek text:</I> &nbsp; <A HREF="http://epigraphy.packhum.org/text/29065">IG_4.1.624</A>
<BR><I>Date:</I> &nbsp; &nbsp; after 182 B.C.
<BR><I>Format:</I> &nbsp; see <A HREF="../../info/translate_key.html">key to translations</A></P>

<P> <I>Lykortas, the father of the historian Polybios, was general of the Achaean League in 182 B.C., in which year he brought Sparta and Messene back into membership of the league ( <A HREF="http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Polybius/23*.html#16">Polyb_23.16-18</A> ).</I>

<HR>

<P> The city of <A CLASS="help" HREF="../../names/s/sparta.html#1">Lakedaimon</A> <I>honours</I> <A CLASS="help" HREF="../../names/l/lycortas.html#1">Lykortas</A> of <A CLASS="help" HREF="../../names/m/megalopolis.html#1">Megalopolis</A>, the son of Thearidas, on account of his virtue and the goodwill that he continually shows towards <I>the city</I>.

<P ALIGN="CENTER">&rarr; <A HREF="s627.html">inscription 627</A>
